sentences: Tosca Berger Kramer (June 17, 1903 – December 27, 1976) was a New Zealand-born American violinist and violist.
In the 1920s a U.S. tour by Berger, who was traveling with her parents, was suspended when Kurt Berger fell ill in Tulsa, Oklahoma.
She was also survived by her mother (Lucy Emma Berger) who was five months from her 100th birthday.
